@startuml TestingLayer4Components
' SPEC source: internal/tmux/e2e_test.go
' Layer 4 — the promptful agent-E2E topology (headless tmux + local model).
!includeurl https://raw.githubusercontent.com/proveo-ca/identity/refs/heads/main/proveo.iuml
skinparam componentStyle rectangle
skinparam shadowing false
skinparam packageStyle rectangle

title Layer 4 · Agent E2E (promptful) — components (PROVEO_LLM_TEST=1)

actor "E2E test / CI" as Test <<actor>>

node "Host" as Host <<node>> {
  component "tmux session (headless PTY)\nnew-session -d · send-keys · capture-pane" as Tmux <<app>>
  component "Ollama (host)\ngemma4:latest models" as HostOllama <<app>>
  database "output bind mount\nDONE.txt (side effect)" as Out <<storage>>
}

node "Docker · per-session agent network" as Dnet <<node>> {
  component "harness TUI (docker run -it)\nopencode / cecli / echo-agent fixture" as Harness <<container>>
  component "Ollama sidecar\nserves host models (read-only)" as Sidecar <<container>>
}

Test --> Tmux : Start / SendText(prompt) / WaitFor
Tmux --> Harness : drive via the -it PTY
HostOllama ..> Sidecar : models mounted read-only
Harness --> Sidecar : model call — NO_PROXY (/v1/chat/completions)
Harness --> Out : writes DONE.txt
Test --> Out : poll + assert marker

note bottom of Dnet
The `--local-model` bridge points the harness at the Ollama sidecar (keyless,
offline, hermetic). Every other destination stays subject to the egress proxy;
only the model call bypasses it via NO_PROXY. gemma4 is a thinking model reached
over the OpenAI-compatible endpoint — so the test asserts the **side effect**.
end note

note right of Test
Skips unless tmux + docker + Ollama(model) present.
Real harnesses via PROVEO_TEST_TARGET; default is the
defs/tests/echo-agent fixture (no vendor image needed).
end note
@enduml
